  "prompt": "Why was MM kalburgi killed?",
  "response": "M.M. Kalburgi, a renowned Indian scholar and writer, was assassinated on August 30, 2015, at his residence in Dharwad, Karnataka. The primary reason attributed to his killing was his controversial writings and public statements, which were seen as critical of certain religious and cultural practices, particularly those associated with Hindutva ideology.\n\nKalburgi was known for his rationalist views and had openly criticized idol worship and other religious practices. His works and speeches often challenged orthodox beliefs, which led to significant backlash from conservative and right-wing groups. The assailants were believed to be associated with such groups, motivated by their opposition to Kalburgi's views.\n\nThe case drew national attention and was linked to a series of attacks on rationalist thinkers in India, including the murders of Narendra Dabholkar and Govind Pansare. In 2022, the National Investigation Agency (NIA) arrested and charged two individuals, Amol Kale and Amit Degvekar, in connection with Kalburgi's murder, linking them to a broader conspiracy involving these other killings.\n\nThe assassination of M.M. Kalburgi remains a poignant example of the tensions between free speech, rationalism, and religious orthodoxy in India.",
